  "prompt": "Why am I blocked from asking questions under anonymous basis on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you are blocked from asking questions anonymously on Quora:\n\n1. **Violation of Community Guidelines**: If you have previously violated Quora's community guidelines or terms of service, your ability to post anonymously may have been restricted. This can include posting inappropriate content, spamming, or harassment.\n\n2. **Suspicious Activity**: If your account has exhibited behavior that Quora's automated systems flag as suspicious, such as rapidly posting questions or engaging in unusual activity patterns, you might be restricted from certain actions, including posting anonymously.\n\n3. **Past Abuse**: If you've used the anonymous feature to bypass rules or engage in behavior that was flagged by moderators, Quora may place limitations on your account to prevent future abuse.\n\n4. **Technical Issues**: Sometimes, technical issues with the website or app could temporarily prevent users from accessing certain features, including posting anonymously.\n\n5. **Policy Changes**: Quora may have updated its policies or features. Sometimes platforms adjust how they handle anonymity to improve overall user experience and community safety.\n\nIf you believe you were blocked unfairly or if you need clarification on the specific reason for the restriction, you can contact Quora\u2019s support team for more information.",
